Four men charged after more than $100k worth of pot seized in Sumter

by Matthew Stevens

Thu, March 10th 2016 at 6:38 PM
5
VIEW ALL PHOTOS
100k worth of marijuana seized.JPG

SUMTER COUNTY, SC (WACH) - Four people are in jail after deputies discoverd more than $100,000 worth of marijuana.

Rondell Harriet, 23, of Sumter, Cedrick Mobley, 26, Gary Watts, 51, and Clifton Price, 26, all of Mississippi are facing drug charges after a bust Wednesday.

Deputies responded to Sumter motel after receiving activity about possible drug activity at the location.

Deputies arrived and seized more than 24 packages of marijuana and $26,000 cash.

All four men are being held at the Sumter-Lee Regional Detention Center.
